    All Classes and Interfaces

    Class
    Description
    AbandonedShip
    The AbandonedShip class is a type of Card that implements specific effects within a game.
    AbandonedStation
    Represents an Abandoned Station card in the game.
    AcceptClient
    The AcceptClient class represents a specific state in the game where the client can either accept or decline a particular action.
    AcceptCommand
    The AcceptCommand class is a specific implementation of the Command class that handles acceptance-related logic during game execution.
    Accepting
    The Accepting class represents a specific state of a player in the game where the player has the ability to accept or decline certain game-related actions.
    AddCrewAction
    AddCrewAction represents an action where crew members consisting of humans and/or aliens are added to a housing unit.
    AddCrewClient
    The AddCrewClient class is responsible for handling the "Add Crew" state during the game.
    AddCrewCommand
    Represents a command to add crew members to a player's game board.
    AddCrewState
    Represents the state of a player when they are allowed to add crew members to their game board.
    AddGoodAction
    This class represents an action to add a specified good to storage or a player board.
    AlienAddons
    Represents a specific type of Component known as AlienAddons.
    ASCII_ART
    ASCII_ART class provides utility methods and fields related to ASCII representation and composition of various game elements, phases, and titles.
    BackgroundGenerator
    The BackgroundGenerator class provides functionality to generate random symbols with special attributes.
    BaseState
    BaseState represents a specific state of a player in the game.
    BaseStateClient
    The BaseStateClient class extends PlayerStateClient and represents the base state of the client-side game logic.
    BLUE
    Represents the "BLUE" type of goods in the system.
    BuildingClient
    Represents a client state for the "Building" phase of the game.
    BuildingCommand
    BuildingCommand represents a specific type of command that is used for managing and executing actions related to building operations in the game.
    BuildingShip
    Represents the state in which a player is constructing a ship.
    CANNON
    The CANNON class represents a type of connector for tiles in the game and implements the Connectors interface.
    Card
    Represents a generic card in the game, serving as the base class from which specific card types inherit.
    CardEvent
    Represents a specific type of event that pertains to a card-related action or state within the system.
    CardListner
    CardListner is an interface that defines methods to handle events related to card operations.
    CardsController
    The CardsController class extends the abstract Controller class, responsible for managing the game actions and states related to the player's interaction with card-based mechanics.
    CardStacks
    The CardStacks class represents a collection of card stacks and decks used for game mechanics, such as visible and hidden cards, and allows for card management and game level adjustments.
    CheckValidity
    The CheckValidity class represents a specific state in the player's lifecycle, inheriting from the abstract PlayerState class.
    CheckValidityClient
    The CheckValidityClient class is a concrete implementation of the PlayerStateClient abstract class.
    CheckValidityController
    The CheckValidityController class is responsible for handling game actions specific to the "Check Validity" state of a Player.
    ChoosePosition
    The ChoosePosition class is a specific state implementation extending the PlayerState abstract class.
    ChoosePositionClient
    Represents a specific client-side state during the game where a player is required to choose a position.
    ChoosePositionController
    The ChoosePositionController class is a specific implementation of the abstract Controller class.
    ChoosingPlanet
    The ChoosingPlanet class represents the player state where a player is in the process of selecting a planet.
    ChoosingPlanetClient
    The ChoosingPlanetClient class represents the client state where a player is in the process of selecting a planet during the game.
    ChoosingPlanetsCommand
    Represents a command that allows a player to choose a planet during gameplay.
    Client
    The Client class is responsible for handling the communication between the client and the server, managing the player's view and events, and coordinating game logic on the client side.
    ClientInterface
    The ClientInterface defines the contract for client-side operations in a remote system using Java RMI.
    Command
    Represents a base abstract class for all game commands, providing a framework for various command types within the game system.
    CommandCompleter
    The CommandCompleter class is responsible for autocompleting command-line inputs using a predefined set of commands and their corresponding descriptions.
    CommandInterpreter
    The CommandInterpreter class is responsible for parsing and interpreting command strings, converting them into appropriate Command objects for execution.
    CommandInterpreter.CommandCreator
     
    Component
    Abstract base class representing a component in the game.
    ComponentAction
    ComponentAction is an abstract class that provides a framework for implementing actions performed on various components within the game.
    ConcurrentCardListener
    Interface representing a listener for concurrent card events.
    ConnectionRefusedEvent
    Represents an event triggered when a connection attempt is refused.
    Connectors
    Represents a generic connector interface for the game's tile system.
    ConsumeEnergyCommand
    Represents a command to consume energy within the context of the game.
    ConsumingEnergy
    The ConsumingEnergy class represents a state in which the player is performing actions related to energy consumption within the game.
    ConsumingEnergyClient
    ConsumingEnergyClient represents a specific state of a player where energy is being consumed in the game.
    Controller
    The Controller class is an abstract representation of the game's state management and player interaction.
    ControllerHourGlassListener
    Defines an interface for listening to hourglass-related events within the game controller.
    CoveredTileSetEvent
    Represents an event related to a covered tile set in the system.
    DebugShip
    The DebugShip class represents a specialized command in the game to debug and modify the player's ship setup.
    DeckEvent
    Represents an event related to a deck in the system, implementing the Event interface.
    DefendFromLargeCommand
    Represents the DefendFromLargeCommand, a specific type of command that allows players to defend against large scale threats in the game.
    DefendFromSmallCommand
    Represents a command to defend a player from small-scale threats in the game.
    DefendingFromLarge
    Represents the "Defending From Large" state of a player in the game.
    DefendingFromLargeClient
    Represents the defensive state of a player when defending against a large attack, extending the PlayerStateClient abstract class.
    DefendingFromSmall
    * Represents the "DefendingFromSmall" state of a player in the game.
    DefendingFromSmallClient
    The DefendingFromSmallClient class represents the player's state during a small-scale defense scenario within the game.
    DisconnectedClient
    The DisconnectedClient class represents a client that is currently disconnected in the system.
    DOUBLE
    The DOUBLE class represents a type of connector for tiles in the game and implements the Connectors interface.
    DynamicCompleter
    The DynamicCompleter interface extends the Completer interface to provide functionality for dynamic command-line auto-completion.
    ENGINE
    The ENGINE class represents a type of connector for tiles in the game and implements the Connectors interface.
    Epidemic
    The Epidemic class extends Card and represents a specific card in the game that triggers an epidemic event.
    Event
    The Event interface represents a generic type of event within the system.
    EventVisitor
    This interface defines a visitor for processing various types of events within a system using the visitor design pattern.
    ExceptionEvent
    Represents an event related to an exception in the system.
    ExceptionListener
    The ExceptionListener interface should be implemented by any class that wishes to be notified of exceptions occurring during the execution of a program.
    FinishBuildingCommand
    The FinishBuildingCommand class represents a specific type of game command that allows a player to finalize the construction of a building.
    FinishGameEvent
    Represents an event that indicates the end of a game.
    FinishListener
    An interface used for handling game finish events.
    FinishStateClient
    Represents the finish state of a player during the game.
    FlightController
    The FlightController class is a specific implementation of the Controller class that represents a phase in the game where a player transitions through the "Flight" state.
    GAGen
    GAGen class is responsible for loading and managing decks of tiles and cards used in the application.
    Game
    Represents a game session.
    GameBoard
    Represents the main game board managing the players, positions, tiles, and gameplay mechanics.
    GameBoardEvent
    Represents an event on the game board.
    GameBoardListener
    Represents a listener interface for monitoring changes in the game board.

    The GameController class is responsible for managing the game's main state, including player interactions, commands, and overall game flow.

    Represents an event for a game lobby, which includes the list of players and their readiness statuses.
    GameLobbyListener
    Represents a listener interface for receiving notifications about changes in the state of a game lobby.
    GamesHandler
    The GamesHandler class is responsible for managing the lifecycle of games, handling player initialization, processing login requests, managing game controllers, and communication between players and games.
    GetEnginePower
    GetEnginePower is an implementation of the ComponentAction class and is used to calculate the total engine power from visited components while maintaining a count of specific engine types.
    GetGoodAction
    GetGoodAction represents an action to retrieve a good from a storage component and manages interactions and validations related to this operation.
    GetPlasmaDrillPower
    GetPlasmaDrillPower is a subclass of ComponentAction that calculates the total power of plasma drills by visiting PlasmaDrill components in a player state.
    GhListener
    The GhListener interface provides methods to handle events related to the management of the game lobby and player actions.
    GiveAttack
    The GiveAttack class represents a specific state of a player in the game where the player can initiate an attack action.
    GiveAttackClient
    This class represents the client state for handling the "Give Attack" action in the game.
    GiveAttackCommand
    Represents a specific command in the game, used to perform an attack action with optional coordinates.
    GiveSpeed
    The GiveSpeed class represents a specific player state that allows the execution of the GiveSpeedCommand and related actions.
    GiveSpeedClient
    The GiveSpeedClient class is a client-side representation of the "Give Speed" state in the game.
    GiveSpeedCommand
    Represents a command that grants engine power to components on a player's game board.

    Represents a general interface for goods within the system.

    Represents the "GREEN" type of goods in the system.

    Main class that deploys the GUI

    The `GuiRoot` class is responsible for handling the graphical user interface (GUI) and interaction logic for the game application.

    Represents an event associated with a hand in the context of the application.

    The HandleCargoCommand class represents a command in the game responsible for handling various cargo-related actions.

    The HandleDestruction class represents a specific state of the player during the game, where the player has to handle the aftermath of destruction events such as meteor strikes.
    HandleDestructionClient
    The HandleDestructionClient class is responsible for managing the state of handling ship destruction in the game.
    HandleTheft
    The HandleTheft class is a concrete implementation of the PlayerState class, responsible for handling specific behaviors and states associated with theft-related actions in the game.
    HandleTheftClient
    The HandleTheftClient class extends the PlayerStateClient to represent the state where the player is handling a theft scenario in the game.
    HandListener
    The HandListener interface is used to listen for changes or updates to a hand event.
    HotWaterHeater
    The HotWaterHeater class represents a special type of component that can be added to or removed from a player's board in a game.
    Hourglass
    The Hourglass class simulates the behavior of an hourglass timer, capable of counting down a defined duration, managing a fixed number of usages, and notifying listeners about hourglass-related events.
    HourglassEvent
    Represents an hourglass-related event in the system.

    Represents an abstract housing unit within a tile-based game board.

    Thrown to indicate that a housing unit is unexpectedly empty.

    Thrown to indicate that an attempted action cannot be performed because it is impossible under the current circumstances.
    ImpossibleBoardChangeException
    Thrown to indicate that an attempted modification to a game board cannot be performed because it violates the rules, constraints, or logical structure of the game.
